name: food-ordering-system
description: Food ordering system application in Udemy course: Microservices: Clean Architecture, DDD, SAGA, Outbox & Kafka

name: microservices-dotnet-bank-system
description: .NET Microservices architecture using RabbitMQ for message brokering, PostgreSQL and MongoDB for data management, and tools like pgAdmin and mongo-express for database administration. It includes APIs for account and transaction management, complete with health check endpoints and a custom NuGet package.

name: Cinema-MicroServices
description: The aim of the project is to realize a movie ticket buying simulation project with distributed systems (microservices) with .NET 9 by using the latest technologies.

name: super-loan-backend
description: Backend for super loan microservice system

name: eCommerce-Microservice
description: .Net based mock ecommerce system in a microservices architecture

name: config-mancer
description: configuration storage and delivery system for microservices

name: MessDFS
description: Distributed File System built in a Microservices environment.

name: HealthCare_System
description: The Healthcare Management System is a distributed, scalable, and microservices-based application developed in Python using FastAPI. The system facilitates the management of patients, doctors, appointments, and notifications in a modern healthcare setting. Each microservice operates independently and communicates asynchronously via RabbitMQ.

name: microservices-with-fastapi
description: The project demonstrates a microservices architecture using FastAPI and Redis Streams. It showcases a modern approach to developing asynchronous, scalable, and resilient systems using RESTful APIs and event-driven communication.  This repository complements the Medium article.

name: phluxor-remote
description: Phluxor Remote is a library that allows you to create remote actor systems in Phluxor.

name: Exception-Handler
description: This is custom spring starter which handle all the exception raised by the microservices in hospital management system

name: Zesty
description: Zesty is an order management system built with Go microservices, using gRPC for inter service communication, RabbitMQ for messaging and MongoDB for data storag

name: MachineLearning-PeerToPeer
description: Machine learning pipeline with stacking ensemble models deployed as Dockerized microservices. Includes Flask-based APIs for distributed predictions and a central server for aggregation. Scalable, modular, and ideal for exploring ML and distributed systems integration.

name: StockMaster-
description: An ongoing cloud computing project for managing stock market data using microservices architecture. Features real-time HTTP request handling, integration with MongoDB for multiple collections, and scalable design. Demonstrates skills in distributed systems, API communication, and database-driven development.

name: MultiShop
description: This project is an e-commerce website developed using **microservice architecture**. Data is managed using **PostgreSQL** and **MongoDB** databases, while communication between system components is handled via **API**. The scalable and performance-oriented structure provides a flexible and sustainable solution.

name: EA-CustomerService
description: This project is a microservice that is part of the EA eCommerce system. It provides a Customer Management API built with .NET, following CQRS, Clean Architecture, and Clean Code principles. The service communicates using RPC messaging via RabbitMQ and EasyNetQ.

name: AuctionHouse
description: This project implements a scalable and modular microservice architecture designed for efficient development, deployment, and maintenance of modern web applications. The core technologies used include Next.js for the frontend, .NET for backend services, and Docker for containerization and orchestration of the entire system.
